  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Perren is a very popular, traditional, family-run hotel with a relaxed and friendly atmosphere. It offers comfortable accommodation and good cuisine, all in a great location just a few minutes’ walk to the village centre and nearest lift.</p>
<h2>Family run</h2>
<p>The Hotel Perren is a traditional hotel, run by the same family since 1956. The hotel offers comfortable accommodation with a central location, each room varies in décor, however maintain a traditional style with the use of wood and comfortable furniture. Many of the bedrooms have incredible views of Zermatt and the iconic Matterhorn mountain, many of the rooms also have balconies so you can soak up the winter sun.</p>
<h2>Food and drink</h2>
<p>The <span>Alpine Brasserie La Barrique is a intimate bistro style restaurant serving classics with a twist and French dishes, plus the extensive wine menu pairs well with the offering. If you want to dine in a more intimate setting, up to eight people can dine in La Cave, the hotels wine cellar - ask the wait staff for the best wine pairings, they definitely have a wide variety. For a truly unique experience, the Fondue Gondola is an excellent choice - dine in one of the former Zermatt gondolas and enjoy authentic Swiss fondue in a great setting.</span></p>
<p><span>The Q-Staff Bar provides a cosy place to relax and unwind after a day of exploring Zermatt, with a selection of wines, cocktail classics, draft beer and non-alcoholic drinks - it is a great spot to share stories with your family and new found friends.</span></p>
<h2>Sustainable stays</h2>
<p>The Hotel Perren is on the route to offering sustainable stays, housekeeping is provided daily but they ask that you hang the green card on your door, plus daily linen changes are offered on request - saving electric and detergent. Plus meals are created with fresh and local produce from local suppliers. </p>]]></description>
